OL,4,CChina's new 'tang ping' trend aims to
OL,5,Chighlight pressures of work culture
OL,6, Young people in China exhausted by a
OL,7, culture of hard work with seemingly
OL,8, little reward are highlighting the need
OL,9, for a lifestyle change by "lying flat".
OL,11,FThe new trend, known as "tang ping", is
OL,12,Fdescribed as an antidote to society's
OL,13,Fpressures to find jobs and perform well
OL,14,Fwhile working long shifts.
OL,16,FChina has a shrinking labour market and
OL,17,Fyoung people often work more hours.
OL,19,FThe term "tang ping" is believed to
OL,20,Fhave originated in a post on a popular
OL,21,FChinese social media site.
